The paper deals with the use of quadrotor drones and computer vision to learn collective behavior, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of convolutional neural networks to process visual inputs and generate control commands is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of weakly supervised saliency maps, which is a topic in both computer vision and machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with the coordination and control of multiple agents, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
